  "prompt": "How many rounds of admission will be conducted for an MBA at NIT Trichy?",
  "response": "As of the latest available information up to October 2023, the **MBA program at NIT Trichy (National Institute of Technology Tiruchirappalli)** typically conducts **two rounds of admission** based on the candidate's entrance exam scores (e.g., CAT, CMAT, or GMAT). The admission process generally includes:\n\n1. **Shortlisting of candidates** based on their entrance exam scores.\n2. **Group Discussion (GD) and Personal Interview (PI)** rounds for shortlisted candidates.\n3. **Final selection** based on a composite score, which includes:\n   - Entrance exam score.\n   - Performance in GD and PI.\n   - Academic profile and work experience (if applicable).\n\nIt is important to check the official NIT Trichy website or admission brochure for the most accurate and up-to-date details, as the admission process may vary slightly from year to year.",
